            "chars": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>LD.XVII.R14</em></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Merdle dead by his own hand</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-bc8318e1-7fff-3503-f361-fd949537b5a6\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is a summary rather than a quotation from the text, which instead includes the lines &ldquo;Mr Merdle is dead&rdquo; and &ldquo;Mr Merdle has destroyed himself&rdquo; (LD 688). Curiously, the phrase &ldquo;his own hand,&rdquo; while not used in this chapter to refer to his suicide, does appear at the close of the previous chapter when Merdle shakes Fanny&rsquo;s hand: &ldquo;Where his own hand had shrunk to, was not made manifest&rdquo; (683).</p>"
